## M24: arity mismatch at the call site is rejected at sema time.
##
## `cb: *Closure1(Int)` declares a one-arg callback; calling it
## with zero or two args fires a tailored arity diagnostic before
## the Zig backend ever sees the call.

sub main()
  v: *Cell(Int) = *Cell(value: 0)
  cb: *Closure1(Int) = *Closure1(Int)(|+v| (a: Int) v.set(a))
  cb()                        # error: expects 1 argument(s); got 0
  cb(1, 2)                    # error: expects 1 argument(s); got 2
